Myth: Joining the PTC means I‚Äôm automatically signed up to volunteer for everything.
Reality: No way. We all have lives, hockey practice, dinner, work. Joining the PTC means you‚Äôre in the know on what‚Äôs going on. post_text:
Meet the 2020-2021 PTC Board!

Introducing Libby Dominik, President:

Libby is new to the PTC this year, but she's been volunteering in the classrooms for the last couple years. Her and her husband have two kiddos - Mae, going into third grade and Hamilton, going into first grade. In her free time, Libby likes to read, cross-stitch, watch SVU, and go to bed early - she's basically an 80-year-old trapped in a forty-something body! She's looking forward to what this new year might bring for Jeffers Pond, and is excited for the day the kids and staff can all get back to school safely. In the meantime, please reach out with any questions or concerns! You can leave a message on our Facebook page or send an email to info.jefferspondptc@gmail.com.

post_text:
Meet the 2020-2021 PTC Board!

Introducing Pennie Peterson, Secretary:

Pennie comes to the PTC with lots of experience. She has been a part of the PTC for 7 years, and has also been on the board in the past. She loves to be involved and as she sees how fast her kids grow, know these times will come to an end. She says, "Get involved as it goes fast. There is a spot for everyone." She lives in Prior Lake with her husband and two girls, ages 13 and 9, going into 8th and 4th. When she is not volunteering, she works part time and likes boating, hosting friends, baking, game nights, and online shopping.

Meet the 2020-2021 PTC Board!

Introducing Jessie Carney, Co-Volunteer Coordinator:

My name is Jessie Carney, and I‚Äôll be one of the volunteer coordinators for the 2020-2021 school year. My husband, Andy, and I have 3 children. Two will be at JP this year ‚Äì 4th and 5th graders, and one will be at HOMS. I spend a lot of time driving kids to the soccer field and hockey rink. You can find it in the App Store for iOS or Google Play for Android. Open the app and find 'Settings' in the main menu (‚ò∞). This week is volunteer appreciation week. We wanted to send out a big thank you to all of the amazing volunteers that help and support Jeffers Pond Elementary. This shout out goes to the PTC and the DOGS, to the weekly classroom helpers, the field trip volunteers, and all of the other amazing people who do so much for the students and staff at Jeffers Pond.

THANK YOU TO ALL OF OUR KIDS COMPANY STAFF

This week is Afterschool Professionals Week. We want to say a big thank you to Sara and her amazing group for all the love and care you provide before and after school. Thank you for creatively continuing the learning beyond the school day! You are all truly appreciated!

THANK YOU TO OUR ADMINISTRATIVE PROFESSIONALS

This week is administrative professionals week. We want to say a huge thank you to Christine, Marcia, and Joni for all that you do to hold our school together. We truly appreciate all of your care and commitment to helping the Jeffers Pond Community.

PTC Student Directory Opt-in Opportunity:
Good morning Jeffers Pond families,

Our PTC would like to give any families that did not opt in to the school directory this fall a chance to do it at this time. We are hopeful that it will give families a chance to share their information so they can connect with other friends and families electronically while we are doing our distance learning.

If you opted in this fall there is nothing else you need to do. All new information will be added to the current directory and distributed to all participating families.

Please complete the form by clicking the link below. Complete one form per student by April 23rd.

* This is an opt-in directory. You will only receive a copy of the directory if you complete a form for your child(ren) to be included in the directory.

The student directory will be emailed to all participating families after the April 23rd deadline.
Contact jpptc.directory@gmail.com with questions.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1RvXO2HUqPzeameieqzRq4Z7NXIm_Qq6vNgxImFQgneQ/viewform?edit_requested=true

post_text:
5th Grade Families! We need you!

The PTC is looking for a person or people who would like to coordinate the 5th grade farewell celebration that is held in June. The celebration is held in the afternoon on the last week of school. (Day TBD) Responsibilities include collaboration with the teachers, planning and organizing the fun program. There is a small budget and the fun thing is, you get to make it how you want it. There are some past parents who have done this coordinating that would be of assistance if you have any questions. There will be a binder of ideas for you to use as well. This event DOES NOT happen without parent volunteers. If interested, please contact the PTC by leaving a comment or email info.JeffersPondPTC@gmail.com
text:
5th Grade Families! We need you!

The PTC is looking for a person or people who would like to coordinate the 5th grade farewell celebration that is held in June. The celebration is held in the afternoon on the last week of school. (Day TBD) Responsibilities include collaboration with the teachers, planning and organizing the fun program. There is a small budget and the fun thing is, you get to make it how you want it. There are some past parents who have done this coordinating that would be of assistance if you have any questions. There will be a binder of ideas for you to use as well. This event DOES NOT happen without parent volunteers. If interested, please contact the PTC by leaving a comment or email info.JeffersPondPTC@gmail.com

We are looking for volunteers from Jeffers Pond to become a member of Friends of Wolf Ridge. You will meet a few times a year; the first meeting is on Monday, January 13th at 6pm at the Caribou in Prior Lake. This organization supports Prior Lake continuing to have fifth graders go to Wolf Ridge year after year. They support this program through letter writing, writing grants, spreading the word, marketing, and many other ways. If you are interested in becoming a member of this important group, please contact Jeffers Pond at 952-226-0600.
#jefferspondptc

post_text:
The Jeffers Pond PTC is selling the Minnesota Weatherguide Environment Calendar and Almanac to raise funds to support the Jr. Naturalist Program and environmental education opportunities for Preschool thru 5th grade students at Jeffers Pond. Weatherguide calendars make memorable gifts for parents, grandparents, aunts, uncles, friends, colleagues and co-workers, party hosts, and nature enthusiasts.

$10 from every purchase goes back to Jeffers Pond!

For details, see the flyer attached. Calendars are for sale now, Thursday, November 14 thru Tuesday, November 26th (including during conferences.) in the Jeffers Pond Elementary Office. Calendars will be sent home with students OR available for pickup starting Monday, December 2nd.
#jefferspondptc
